elements.title: Jorge Meléndez
elements.contents: ... that Jorge Meléndez (pictured) was appointed as the National Democratic Party's candidate for president of El Salvador in 1919, after both frontrunners suddenly dropped out days before the election?

elements.title: Téléscaphe
elements.contents: ... that the Téléscaphe was an underwater cable car system that allowed tourists to visit the seabed?

elements.title: Olga Olgina
elements.contents: ... that opera singer Olga Olgina used the same stage name as her mother?

elements.title: Ya Laylat al-Eid
elements.contents: ... that "Ya Laylat al-Eid", originally a number in Dananeer, a 1940 musical about a singing slave girl, was removed from the film and had its lyrics changed to better associate it with Eid?

elements.title: Thomas Agni of Lentini
elements.contents: ... that being outranked by Bishop Thomas Agni of Lentini so infuriated the future Pope Urban IV that he left Palestine and went to Rome?

elements.title: her new album
elements.contents: ... that Taylor Swift announced her new album on a sports podcast?

elements.title: an unwitting mafia enforcer
